    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2508</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-16T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1916, 7 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 18, 8.15 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3635. Great prominence given by German press to reports of trouble with Mexico.
                    Several papers think the Japanese are mixed up in the matter and are secretly
                    backing Villa. Resignation of <persName corresp="#p_TAPFV1">Von
                        Tirpitz</persName> now publicly confirmed and <persName corresp="#p_CEV1"
                        >Von Capelle</persName> named as probable successor.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
